WEBVTT

00:06.717 --> 00:09.226
The initial surge failed because
of poor military strategy.

00:09.284 --> 00:11.324
What? No.
The strategy was sound.

00:11.409 --> 00:12.652
The intel was faulty.

00:12.737 --> 00:16.557
Yet, they eventually triumphed
despite inferior technology.

00:16.642 --> 00:17.284
- Right?
- Ah!

00:17.369 --> 00:19.354
Military history buffs, eh?
Well, me, too.

00:19.439 --> 00:20.885
So, what are
we talking about, huh?

00:21.125 --> 00:23.591
Battle of the Bulge?
Battle of Midway?

00:23.676 --> 00:25.301
- Battle of...
- Endor.

00:27.003 --> 00:28.712
Star Wars? Episode VI?

00:28.805 --> 00:31.317
The Rebels' problem
was that Palpatine leaked intel

00:31.402 --> 00:32.856
to the Bothan spies,
and everybody knows that.

00:32.940 --> 00:34.872
That's true, but if the Rebels
had a different attack formation...

00:34.956 --> 00:36.394
Hang on a second.

00:36.813 --> 00:38.772
Are we seriously
debating this?

00:40.948 --> 00:42.934
The Alliance should've bribed
the Hutt syndicate

00:43.019 --> 00:45.660
to start a rebellion, thus
distracting the Imperial armada.

00:45.745 --> 00:46.763
Bing, bang, bong.

00:46.848 --> 00:48.348
Bob's your uncle, 
battle over.

00:49.875 --> 00:51.579
I can't reason with you people.

00:51.750 --> 00:53.580
- I'm out.
- Well, h-hang on a second.

00:53.665 --> 00:55.487
We haven't discussed
the reactor core yet.

00:55.572 --> 00:57.094
Uh, speaking of spies...

00:57.836 --> 00:59.883
I spoke to your father recently.

00:59.967 --> 01:01.261
He's still
pursuing Mason

01:01.346 --> 01:02.581
for burning down the Phoenix.

01:02.665 --> 01:04.572
Uh, why are you talking
to my dad?

01:04.953 --> 01:07.890
Just getting intel on Bishop.
They worked together at DXS.

01:07.975 --> 01:10.197
Right. He tell you
anything interesting?

01:10.281 --> 01:13.708
Hmm, you won't return his calls.
That was interesting.

01:13.793 --> 01:14.981
Well, I generally don't

01:15.066 --> 01:17.364
with people who completely
obliterate my trust.

01:17.449 --> 01:19.769
That's fair enough, but he did
save your life, didn't he?

01:21.734 --> 01:23.696
Well, someone's been
snooping through my file.

01:23.781 --> 01:26.292
Mm. It's not snooping
if you own the company.

01:26.950 --> 01:28.781
You and your father
fell out over a year ago.

01:28.865 --> 01:30.957
Isn't it about time
you kissed and made up?

01:31.041 --> 01:32.219
Time to forgive.

01:32.303 --> 01:34.392
Oh, forgiveness
isn't Mac's strong suit.

01:34.697 --> 01:37.094
Coming from someone who wouldn't
forgive me, that's rich.

01:37.178 --> 01:40.662
If your apology came from you
and not Phil Collins...

01:40.746 --> 01:42.186
His lyrics...
Correction, poetry...

01:42.270 --> 01:43.274
Said everything I wanted to.

01:43.358 --> 01:45.015
They would've been perfect, Mac,

01:45.099 --> 01:47.060
- if I was dating Phil Collins. 
- Hey, do you guys know

01:47.144 --> 01:48.975
where they keep
the parachutes on this plane?

01:49.059 --> 01:50.585
We're fine. It's fine.

01:50.669 --> 01:52.631
Everybody, seat belts on.

