02:02.333 --> 02:04.581
Why'd an F-16 just
give us a flyby?

02:05.198 --> 02:07.253
That fighter jet
was scrambled from Edwards

02:07.338 --> 02:08.473
to check out a ghost plane

02:08.556 --> 02:10.207
just 20 nautical miles

02:10.292 --> 02:12.259
from your position.
Ghost plane?

02:12.343 --> 02:14.660
Does that mean it doesn't
respond to radio communication?

02:14.745 --> 02:15.828
Or cellular.

02:15.912 --> 02:17.996
Air traffic control
says it's a Cessna

02:18.081 --> 02:19.832
208 Caravan registered

02:19.917 --> 02:21.894
to a commercial aircraft
engineer

02:21.979 --> 02:23.488
named Ben Reinman.

02:23.572 --> 02:26.035
Reinman's flight plan shows him
on a day trip starting

02:26.120 --> 02:28.043
and ending at Moorpark Airport,
but he missed

02:28.128 --> 02:30.284
his arrival and just flew by
without any explanation.

02:30.384 --> 02:32.682
Could be terrorism,
a faulty transmitter,

02:32.767 --> 02:34.987
- or anything in between.
- Only one way to find out:

02:35.072 --> 02:36.903
get eyes on the Cessna.
Hence the F-16.

02:36.988 --> 02:39.315
Looping you in
to USAF audio.

02:40.112 --> 02:41.277
<i>Completed flyby.</i>

02:41.361 --> 02:43.847
<i>Cessna's going too slow
to permit clear visual, over.</i>

02:43.932 --> 02:45.763
<i>Repeat, I have no visual.</i>

02:45.964 --> 02:48.056
Turboprops max out
at 180 knots.

02:48.148 --> 02:50.153
An F-16's stall speed is
250.

02:50.237 --> 02:52.262
That pilot can't go slow enough
to check out the Cessna

02:52.346 --> 02:54.175
- or he'll crash.
- What is our stall speed?

02:54.260 --> 02:55.742
170.

02:56.323 --> 02:57.552
I like what you're thinking.

02:57.695 --> 02:59.526
Turn around
and get eyes on that plane.

02:59.611 --> 03:00.729
Excuse me, Matilda,

03:00.814 --> 03:02.550
but as financier
of this operation, I think

03:02.635 --> 03:04.932
the expenditure of the
jet fuel is up to me.

03:08.399 --> 03:10.358
Turn around and get eyes
on that plane.

03:20.526 --> 03:22.098
We have visual.

03:22.182 --> 03:23.229
You see the pilot?

03:23.313 --> 03:24.440
Yep.

03:24.880 --> 03:27.187
But he's not flying the plane.

03:27.778 --> 03:29.253
Then who is?

03:30.143 --> 03:31.776
No one.

03:34.573 --> 03:36.307
He looks unconscious.

03:36.624 --> 03:38.253
The plane must be on autopilot.

03:38.546 --> 03:39.769
If he doesn't wake up

03:39.854 --> 03:40.852
before that plane
runs out of fuel,

03:40.937 --> 03:41.981
he's gonna fall out of the sky.

03:42.065 --> 03:43.508
Oh, it gets worse.

03:44.883 --> 03:47.538
There's a kid in there.

03:49.685 --> 03:52.987
Oh, yes.
That is worse.

04:14.589 --> 04:16.281
<font color=#FF00FF>*MAcGYVER (2016)*</font>

04:16.366 --> 04:17.916
